Cook the rice: Bring 1 cup water and a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, cover, and reduce to a low simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender.

Wash and dry all produce. Thinly slice the @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced, greens reserved and whites reserved for another use). Thinly slice the @Radishes{3}(thinly sliced). Finely mince or grate @Garlic{1/4%tsp}(finely minced or grated). Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1/2%tsp}(peeled and minced or grated).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, a pinch of garlic (to taste), a pinch of ginger (to taste), and @White Wine Vinegar{1/2%tsp}. Thin with about @water{1%tsp} to reach a drizzling consistency. Season with @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Taste and adjust with more ginger, garlic, or vinegar, if desired.

Season the @Tuna{12%oz} on both sides with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Press the @Sesame Seeds{3%tbsp} onto both sides of the tuna to adhere. Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add the tuna to the pan. Cook about ~{1%minute} per side, until golden brown on the outside but still very rare on the inside.

> TIP: If you'd like your tuna less rare, lower the heat and cook a couple minutes longer.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together the @Arugula{2%oz}, radishes, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, and a drizzle of @White Wine Vinegar{}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Serve: Thinly slice the tuna. Plate the tuna on a bed of rice with the salad on the side. Drizzle with the aioli, and garnish with scallion greens. Enjoy!